# Room Name - TryHackMe: The Greenholt Phish
Date: 16 March 2026
Difficulty: Easy
Category: Phishing Analysis / Email Forensics

# Scenario
Use the knowledge attained to analyze a malicious email. The challenge involved examining a suspicious .eml file to extract key indicators of compromise including sender details, email headers, attachment metadata, and threat intelligence from VirusTotal.

# Tools Used
- TryHackMe Attack Box
- Email Client (.eml viewer)
- Email Source / Header Viewer
- MX Toolbox (SPF / DMARC checker)
- VirusTotal
- Terminal (sha256sum)

# What I Did
- Accessed the TryHackMe machine and opened the challenge.eml file.
- Located the transfer reference number mentioned in the email body: 09674321
- Identified the sender's name from the email signature: Mr. James Jackson
- Found the sender's email address from the From field: info@mutawamarine.com
- Found the Reply-To address, which differed from the sender field indicating reply hijacking: info.mutawamarine@mail.com
- Viewed the raw source of the email and extracted the originating IP address from the email headers: 192.119.71.157
- Looked up the domain associated with the originating IP and identified the owner: Hostwinds LLC
- Used MX Toolbox SPF checker to retrieve the SPF record for the domain: v=spf1 include:spf.protection.outlook.com -all
- Used MX Toolbox to retrieve the DMARC record: v=DMARC1; p=quarantine; fo=1
- Found the name of the malicious attachment in the email: SWT_#09674321____PDF__.CAB
- Ran sha256sum on the attachment file in the terminal to obtain its hash: 2e91c533615a9bb8929ac4bb76707b2444597ce063d84a4b33525e25074fff3f
- Uploaded the hash to VirusTotal and checked the Details tab to find the file size: 400.26 KB
- Identified the true file type from VirusTotal Details tab: RAR

